result.name: LANDMARK - LANDMARK ATRIUM

reviews.text: One of the famous shopping malls in Hong Kong. It is very spacious shopping mall spread across multiple floors. You will find many international brands shops here. Easy to reach via Central MTR station. Good meeting place. There are good number of restaurants also.

This is a very elegant and exclusive restaurant which serves beautifully prepared local food and the service is outstanding. Both the food and the drinks were of high quality. The waiter was attentive, friendly and helpful when going through the menu. His recommendations were excellent and according to what we desired. The price level is rather high, but you pay for what you get. 

Please press the like button :)

Large and very spacious shopping mall spread out over multiple floors. Primarily focusing on luxury shopping brands and non-chain snacks and food, visiting here and spending money can be for rather nice special occasions. Directly connected to the Central station MTR exits, and also the centre of walkways to multiple other malls in Central, this is a place with a lot of foot traffic though, so make sure you go with the flow if you're just passing through. Signage can be very confusing though, so you might need to walk around to find where you need to go.

Landmark is a famous shopping mall located in Central. Its upper floors are all office, while the lower floors are restaurants and famous shops. Here you can see a lot of luxury items such as designer handbags, fashions and jewelry. These items are very expensive and cannot be afforded by ordinary people.
Most renown brands are in this place, and it has a lots of cafe area. Center piece display at the water fountain is also something local tourist love to visit.
